UNITED STATES v. NEW YORK & P. R. S. S. CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. December 15, 1913.) No. 204. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Action at law by the United States against the New York & Porto Rico Steamship Company. Judgment for defendant, and the United States bring error. Affirmed. See, also, 206 Fed. 443. A. S. Pratt, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City.

Before LACOMBE, COXE, and WARD, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court.
